page.title: 05HOLT FOREST
page.content: Holt Forest is a very interesting place. Many different flowers grow here, like the greater stitchwort, bluebells, buttercups, dandelions, gorse, nettles, brambles, primroses, speedwell, celendine, cumfrey, dock, cuckoo pint, ivy, fern, wood, anemone, wood sorrel, wood garlic, cow parsley, clover, tufted vetch and daisy. The trees which grow here are silver birch, yew, sycamore, hazel, beech, hawthorn, willow, wild cherry and privet. Also a few pink campians grow by the road and in the forest. The area of the forest is 2791250 square feet and in the centre is a place called The Glen, a farm which is owned by Mr Hiscock. Another farm nearby is called Pondhead Poultry Farm, and the owner, Mr Batten, has lived there all his life.
